00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:49,840
The black one.

262
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:25,920
l hate this tie!
lt don't match what l got on!

263
00:34:26,240 --> 00:34:27,720
l had a blue one--

264
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:30,560
Damn!

265
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:10,920
She said she write, but she never write.

266
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:14,120
She said only death
could keep her from me.

267
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:17,000
Maybe she dead.

268
00:35:27,720 --> 00:35:29,800
Sofia, slow down!

269
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:32,520
Harpo, l declare, you is slow today!

270
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:38,920
Dear God, Harpo be in love
with a girl called Sofia.

271
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:41,480
Now she be a big girl.

272
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:44,520
Mister say he want to have a look at her.

273
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:47,080
I seen 'em coming way up the road.

274
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:50,120
Theyjust be marching, like going to war.

275
00:35:56,160 --> 00:35:57,920
This here is Sofia.

276
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:02,120
Sofia is a pretty name, huh?
Sofia, Sofia, Sofia!

277
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:04,120
Us gonna get married.

278
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:09,760
Looks like you got yourself in trouble.

279
00:36:10,120 --> 00:36:11,720
l ain't in no trouble.

280
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:13,640
Big, though.

281
00:36:13,960 --> 00:36:15,240
Who the daddy?

282
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:17,160
Harpo.

283
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:19,040
How does he know that?

284
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:22,440
He knows because he the only one!

285
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:27,880
Get me some lemonade.

286
00:36:29,480 --> 00:36:31,400
Young women no good these days.

287
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:34,600
Got their legs open
for every Tom, Dick and Harpo.

288
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:46,280
Don't think l'll let
my boy marry you 'cause...

289
00:36:46,560 --> 00:36:48,120
...you in the family way.

290
00:36:48,200 --> 00:36:49,520
Not cold enough.

291
00:36:49,640 --> 00:36:54,280
He young and limited. Pretty gal like
you could put anything over on him.

292
00:36:56,840 --> 00:37:00,840
Why l need to marry Harpo?
He living here with you.

293
00:37:01,160 --> 00:37:03,880
What food and clothes he get, you buy.

294
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:09,160
l know your daddy throwed you out.
Ready to live in the street.

295
00:37:10,440 --> 00:37:13,480
No, sir, l ain't living in no streets.

296
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:16,360
l'm living with my sister and her husband.

297
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:20,040
l can live with them
the rest of my life if l want.

298
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:23,720
Don't tell me how to take care
of me and my baby.

299
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:26,280
l can take care of it myself.

300
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:28,000
Nice visiting.

301
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:30,400
You stay right here, Harpo.

302
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:33,960
When you free,
me and the baby will be waiting.

303
00:37:40,040 --> 00:37:43,560
At least somebody here know
how to treat a visitor.

304
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:46,880
Harpo, don't you move...

305
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:49,160
...one step.

306
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:54,120
Don't make me wait too long.

307
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:04,200
l won't!

308
00:38:04,680 --> 00:38:05,360
l will!

309
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:06,400
l do.

310
00:38:06,680 --> 00:38:07,640
l do!

311
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:09,120
l do.

312
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:13,720
Do you take this man to be
your lawful wedded husband?

313
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:18,440
To love, honor and cherish?
Forsaking all others for him alone...

314
00:38:18,760 --> 00:38:21,960
...you will perform unto him
all duties owed a husband...

315
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,360
...until death shall separate you.

316
00:38:24,640 --> 00:38:25,520
l do!

317
00:38:27,560 --> 00:38:29,640
You may now salute the bride.

318
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:32,800
Amen!

319
00:38:37,640 --> 00:38:40,520
l's married now! l's a married woman!

320
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:28,040
l been needing so many curtains,
but l ain't had time.

321
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:30,440
You children go on home!

322
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:33,560
Harpo, come on down.
l need you to hold this baby.

323
00:39:33,880 --> 00:39:35,000
l'm busy!

324
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:37,800
Busy making a racket.
Now come on down here!

325
00:39:38,120 --> 00:39:41,640
Damn, l'll come down
when l'm good and ready!

326
00:39:49,160 --> 00:39:51,880
Child, we're going to get you a little milk.

327
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:55,080
A little milk for the baby, yes, indeed.

328
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:57,160
Here. Go to your daddy.

329
00:39:57,480 --> 00:39:59,160
What should l do with it?

330
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:02,720
Feed her, then fix up the mess you done.

331
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:04,760
l can smell the rain coming.

332
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:09,480
Miss Celie, we got ourselves some new
curtains l want to put in the bedroom.

333
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,160
What you looking at?

334
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:17,320
lt's gonna rain on your head!

335
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:19,720
You ever hit her?

336
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:22,600
No, sir.

337
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:25,800
How do you expect her to mind?

338
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:28,360
Wives is like children.

339
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:32,240
You have to let them know
who got the upper hand.

340
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:35,240
Nothing can do it better
than a good beating.

341
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:39,400
Sofia thinks too much of herself.

342
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:42,080
Needs to be taken down a peg or two.

343
00:40:47,720 --> 00:40:50,280
Got a new baby and it cry all night long.

344
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:53,320
Kept him up so he said
he wasn't going to work.

345
00:40:53,640 --> 00:40:56,680
She got all upset but l said,
leave the man alone.

346
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:59,320
Sometimes a man just needs
to be left alone.

347
00:40:59,400 --> 00:41:00,760
l want some food!

348
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:04,120
Pie's in the pantry. Women need
to be left alone sometimes, too.

349
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:07,240
l tell Harpo, when l'm fussing,
''leave me alone! ''

350
00:41:07,520 --> 00:41:08,800
Get it for me!

351
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:10,760
What's the matter with you?

352
00:41:10,920 --> 00:41:13,160
That's my own baby crying.

353
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:16,200
Make yourself useful.

354
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:27,240
What should l do about Sofia?

355
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:38,120
Beat her.

356
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:53,800
You told Harpo to beat me!

357
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:59,400
lt was that mule, Old Joey.
Old Joey, the mule.

358
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:03,080
l was plowing the north field
and the mule went crazy.

359
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:06,760
He started kicking.
Busted my eye and my lip.

360
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:09,640
All my life l had to fight.

361
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:13,480
l had to fight my daddy,
l had to fight my uncles.

362
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:15,720
l had to fight my brothers.

363
00:42:16,360 --> 00:42:19,080
Girl child ain't safe in a family of mens.

364
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:22,440
But l never thought l had
to fight in my own house!

365
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:26,600
l loves Harpo.

366
00:42:27,080 --> 00:42:29,160
God knows l do.

367
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:33,480
But l'll kill him dead
before l let him beat me!

368
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:35,560
That's a hoof print.

369
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,240
lt's a fist print.

370
00:42:37,320 --> 00:42:40,040
No, sir. Ain't no fist touched my face.

371
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:43,080
You want a dead son-in-law, Miss Celie?

372
00:42:43,400 --> 00:42:46,120
You keep on advising him like you're doing.

373
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:51,400
This life be over soon.
Heaven lasts always.

374
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:55,560
You should bash Mister's head open
and think about Heaven later.

375
00:43:16,040 --> 00:43:18,120
Sofia beat on Harpo.

376
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:20,680
Then Harpo beat on Sofia.

377
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:23,560
And then, Sofia beat on Harpo some more.

378
00:43:23,880 --> 00:43:27,080
In between the beatings,
the children keep coming.

379
00:43:32,040 --> 00:43:36,000
And then one day,
Sofia can't take it no more.

380
00:43:36,520 --> 00:43:38,120
Good riddance!

381
00:44:08,680 --> 00:44:09,960
Nettie.

382
00:44:32,520 --> 00:44:36,360
l brung you some fresh-baked cookies,
made in my stove!

383
00:44:57,320 --> 00:45:01,480
Have a fine day, Mr. Huntley!
And keep the plate!

384
00:45:06,760 --> 00:45:08,520
Anything come for me?

385
00:45:28,520 --> 00:45:31,880
Dear God, today was a peculiar day.

386
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:36,200
I was sitting on the porch
reading to the kids...

387
00:45:36,520 --> 00:45:39,240
...when suddenly, something struck me.

388
00:45:39,560 --> 00:45:42,120
I got up and looked at the sky.

389
00:45:42,440 --> 00:45:45,000
It was dark and there
wasn't nothing moving.

390
00:45:45,320 --> 00:45:47,240
I got down off the porch...

391
00:45:47,560 --> 00:45:50,920
...to see what was coming.
It felt like twister weather.

392
00:45:51,240 --> 00:45:55,080
I didn't see nothing.
But I know something's there.

393
00:45:55,360 --> 00:45:58,400
Yes, indeed, Lord.
I know something's coming.

394
00:46:27,880 --> 00:46:30,280
Who that, Pa? Who this?

395
00:46:30,600 --> 00:46:32,200
Pa, who this?

396
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:35,480
The woman that should have been
your mammy.

397
00:46:35,560 --> 00:46:36,680
Shug Avery?

398
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:39,680
Give me a hand and get her in the house.

399
00:46:40,680 --> 00:46:43,240
Celie! Help me get her in the house.

400
00:47:04,040 --> 00:47:05,800
Celie! Get here!

401
00:47:11,720 --> 00:47:15,400
This Shug Avery, a friend of the family.
Fix up the spare room.

402
00:47:15,720 --> 00:47:17,000
I can't move.

403
00:47:17,480 --> 00:47:20,360
I can't move! I need to see her eyes.

404
00:47:20,680 --> 00:47:24,040
I feel that once I see her eyes,
my feet can let go...

405
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:26,080
...of where they're stuck.

406
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:36,000
You sure is ugly!

407
00:47:52,200 --> 00:47:54,440
Turn loose my goddamn hand!

408
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:57,480
What's the matter with you? You crazy?

409
00:47:58,280 --> 00:48:00,840
l don't need no weak little boy...

410
00:48:01,160 --> 00:48:04,360
...can't say no to his daddy, hanging on me!

411
00:48:04,840 --> 00:48:07,560
l need me a man! You hear!

412
00:48:08,680 --> 00:48:10,120
A man!

413
00:48:16,840 --> 00:48:21,480
And l don't want to smell
no goddamn stinking pipe, Albert!

414
00:48:25,480 --> 00:48:29,000
Get that thing to make me
something to eat.

415
00:48:29,480 --> 00:48:31,720
No, l'll make it myself.

416
00:48:33,480 --> 00:48:34,760
Albert?

417
00:48:41,160 --> 00:48:42,040
Shit!

418
00:48:48,040 --> 00:48:51,880
Eggs. Skillet. Why are the pots up here?

419
00:48:52,040 --> 00:48:53,680
Nobody can get to them.

420
00:49:06,920 --> 00:49:09,480
Butter, butter, butter.

421
00:49:09,960 --> 00:49:12,040
lt's in the cooler, on the shelf.

422
00:49:14,760 --> 00:49:16,680
Butter? Butter!

423
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:19,400
ln the cooler, on the shelf.

424
00:49:20,640 --> 00:49:21,920
Albert.

425
00:49:27,240 --> 00:49:29,000
How do you work this stove?

426
00:49:30,600 --> 00:49:32,040
Ain't hot enough.

427
00:49:34,760 --> 00:49:37,800
Can't even keep a stove
burning good all day.

428
00:49:38,920 --> 00:49:41,320
She can't even keep her oven hot!

429
00:49:41,960 --> 00:49:43,640
You're useless sometimes!

430
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:48,040
Wood. Wood.

431
00:49:57,000 --> 00:49:59,240
Did you ever cook on this?

432
00:50:03,880 --> 00:50:05,960
lt still ain't hot enough!

433
00:50:13,640 --> 00:50:17,480
l'll get it hot.
l'll show you how to make it...hot.

434
00:50:51,400 --> 00:50:54,440
Baby, look what l brought you.

435
00:50:57,800 --> 00:51:01,480
Have l got a surprise for you.
This'll make you all well.

436
00:51:01,880 --> 00:51:05,040
This looks burnt, but the eggs
are the way you like them.

437
00:51:05,320 --> 00:51:07,400
Are you trying to kill me?

438
00:51:08,200 --> 00:51:10,120
Now, baby, don't be that way!

439
00:52:03,240 --> 00:52:05,800
l told you, l don't want nothing!

440
00:52:08,840 --> 00:52:12,840
Ijust stand back, and wait to see
what the wall will look like.

441
00:52:13,160 --> 00:52:16,520
See what kind of colors
Shug'll put on there now.

442
00:52:37,640 --> 00:52:41,960
What you staring at?
Never seen a naked woman before?

443
00:52:42,600 --> 00:52:44,520
You got any children?

444
00:52:44,880 --> 00:52:46,160
Yes, ma'am.

445
00:52:46,520 --> 00:52:48,520
''Yes, ma'am''? l ain't that old.

446
00:52:49,960 --> 00:52:50,920
Two.

447
00:52:51,560 --> 00:52:52,840
Where they at?

448
00:52:53,640 --> 00:52:54,920
l don't know.

449
00:52:56,360 --> 00:52:57,640
Who are you?

450
00:52:58,920 --> 00:53:00,360
Celie, ma'am.

451
00:53:14,120 --> 00:53:15,720
You ain't well.

452
00:53:16,200 --> 00:53:20,040
Mind your own business. l feel fine.
Just had to eat.

453
00:53:20,360 --> 00:53:23,240
Now, put some more bubbling oil
in this tub.

454
00:53:29,320 --> 00:53:30,920
You got kids?

455
00:53:31,560 --> 00:53:32,840
Yeah.

456
00:53:34,760 --> 00:53:36,840
They with my ma and pa.

457
00:53:37,320 --> 00:53:41,840
Never knowed a child to come out right
unless there's a man around.

458
00:53:45,640 --> 00:53:46,920
Children...

459
00:53:47,560 --> 00:53:49,640
...got to have a pa.

460
00:53:53,320 --> 00:53:54,920
Your pa love you?

461
00:53:57,800 --> 00:53:59,560
My pa loved me.

462
00:54:00,680 --> 00:54:02,600
My pa still loves me...

463
00:54:02,960 --> 00:54:04,680
...except he don't know it.

464
00:54:06,760 --> 00:54:08,120
He don't know it.

465
00:54:48,040 --> 00:54:50,440
Hey, boy! Here, boy!

466
00:54:50,840 --> 00:54:52,720
Nobody here to greet your pa?

467
00:54:54,600 --> 00:54:57,000
Sure ain't nobody in the fields.

468
00:55:35,880 --> 00:55:39,720
Just couldn't rest till you got her
in your house, could you?

469
00:55:42,760 --> 00:55:43,880
Cool drink?

470
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:46,440
Take your hat?

471
00:55:56,360 --> 00:55:59,240
What is it with this Shug Avery?

472
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:02,120
She black as tar...

473
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:04,040
...nappy-headed....

474
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:08,040
She got legs like baseball bats.

475
00:56:08,520 --> 00:56:11,720
Her own daddy won't have
nothing to do with her.

476
00:56:12,200 --> 00:56:14,760
Old Mister talking trash about Shug.

477
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:17,880
Folks don't like nobody
being too proud or too free.

478
00:56:17,960 --> 00:56:21,000
She's no more than a jook-joint Jezebel.

479
00:56:22,280 --> 00:56:24,200
She ain't even clean.

480
00:56:24,520 --> 00:56:28,360
l hear she's got
that nasty women's disease.

481
00:56:29,960 --> 00:56:32,680
You ain't got it in you to understand.

482
00:56:33,640 --> 00:56:35,400
l love Shug Avery.

483
00:56:36,040 --> 00:56:38,120
Always have, always will.

484
00:56:38,440 --> 00:56:41,160
Should've married her when l had a chance.

485
00:56:42,280 --> 00:56:46,920
And throwed your life away. And a right
smart amount of my money with it.

486
00:56:50,640 --> 00:56:54,000
l hear all her children's
got different daddies.

487
00:56:55,240 --> 00:56:58,120
lt's all too trifling and confused.

488
00:56:58,920 --> 00:57:02,440
All Shug's children got the same daddy.
l can vouch--

489
00:57:02,640 --> 00:57:04,360
You can vouch for nothing!

490
00:57:05,640 --> 00:57:10,120
Shug Avery done set the population
of Hartwell County a new high.

491
00:57:12,360 --> 00:57:15,080
You just one of the roosters, boy.

492
00:57:23,560 --> 00:57:25,480
You has my sympathy.

493
00:57:26,760 --> 00:57:31,400
Ain't many women's allow their
husband's whore to lay up in their house.

494
00:57:34,640 --> 00:57:36,360
Hand Pa his hat.

495
00:58:27,080 --> 00:58:30,920
Next time, I'll put a little Shug Avery pee
in his glass...

496
00:58:31,160 --> 00:58:33,000
...and see how he like that.

497
00:58:49,480 --> 00:58:53,000
I ain't heard so much racket
since before Sofia left.

498
00:58:53,400 --> 00:58:55,800
Every evening after he leave the field...

499
00:58:56,160 --> 00:58:59,480
...he knocking down and piling things up.

500
00:58:59,720 --> 00:59:02,280
Sometime his friend, Swain,
come by to help.

501
00:59:09,840 --> 00:59:10,960
Harpo!

502
00:59:15,000 --> 00:59:17,560
Two of them worked long way past supper.

503
00:59:17,880 --> 00:59:21,240
Mister have to call and tell them
to shut up the racket.

504
00:59:23,800 --> 00:59:25,400
What you doing?

505
00:59:25,720 --> 00:59:27,280
Building a jook joint!

506
00:59:27,480 --> 00:59:28,920
Way back here?

507
00:59:29,760 --> 00:59:32,520
Jook joint's supposed to
be way back in the woods.

508
00:59:40,760 --> 00:59:42,680
You never seen this before.

509
00:59:44,760 --> 00:59:46,440
l know what a cow looks like.

510
00:59:46,520 --> 00:59:48,760
You ain't never seen a cow like this.

511
00:59:54,880 --> 00:59:56,960
Ready...one...two...three!

512
01:00:12,280 --> 01:00:14,520
Welcome to Harpo's! l'm Harpo.

513
01:00:28,440 --> 01:00:30,680
Girl, l'd drink your bath water!

514
01:00:32,440 --> 01:00:36,000
Oh, sugar dumpling, let me taste some!

515
01:00:37,560 --> 01:00:40,280
You can catch a fish without a hook, girl.

516
01:01:35,160 --> 01:01:37,880
Looks like Albert brought his maid.

517
01:01:38,200 --> 01:01:42,040
Last time l saw that kind of hat
was at my mama's funeral.

518
01:02:20,760 --> 01:02:23,720
There are only two kinds of children
in this world...

519
