Hey, Shug! Write!

684
01:20:12,820 --> 01:20:14,900
Do good in Chicago, Shug!

685
01:20:28,660 --> 01:20:32,340
Honey, let me see you.
Look at you, you're so sweet.

686
01:20:35,380 --> 01:20:38,260
Leave them folks alone.

687
01:20:40,820 --> 01:20:42,740
Good afternoon, Mr. Mayor.

688
01:20:44,980 --> 01:20:49,460
Look at that!
That's the cutest little face l ever saw.

689
01:20:55,860 --> 01:20:58,300
Millie, always going on over the colored.

690
01:20:58,420 --> 01:21:00,500
Your children are so clean.

691
01:21:00,820 --> 01:21:03,380
Would you like to work for me?
Be my maid?

692
01:21:07,700 --> 01:21:09,300
Hell, no.

693
01:21:11,060 --> 01:21:12,420
What did you say?

694
01:21:12,500 --> 01:21:14,420
Hell, no.

695
01:21:14,900 --> 01:21:16,260
What did she say?

696
01:21:18,100 --> 01:21:20,340
Can't you pump that a little faster?

697
01:21:26,300 --> 01:21:29,180
Gal, what did you say to Miss Millie?

698
01:21:30,460 --> 01:21:31,740
l said, ''Hell--''

699
01:21:37,820 --> 01:21:39,260
No, Miss Sofia!

700
01:21:40,380 --> 01:21:41,700
No, Miss Sofia!

701
01:21:56,060 --> 01:21:57,900
l can't believe you did that!

702
01:21:57,980 --> 01:22:01,820
Get my children out of here!
Take them home!

703
01:22:02,460 --> 01:22:03,980
Get my children out of here!

704
01:22:04,060 --> 01:22:05,980
Who do you think you are!

705
01:22:11,580 --> 01:22:15,100
Don't touch me! Leave me alone!
Don't touch me!

706
01:22:21,020 --> 01:22:23,500
Who do you think you are! You fat nigger!

707
01:22:23,740 --> 01:22:27,100
God, dear God! Sheriff, help me!

708
01:22:52,380 --> 01:22:53,820
Howdy, Mayor.

709
01:22:54,140 --> 01:22:55,260
How are you?

710
01:22:55,460 --> 01:22:56,540
Fine.

711
01:22:56,860 --> 01:22:59,740
-How's the missus?
-She's doing real well.

712
01:23:01,660 --> 01:23:03,940
Let's see what we have here.

713
01:23:14,980 --> 01:23:16,420
l'm driving!

714
01:23:16,740 --> 01:23:17,900
l'm driving.

715
01:23:25,700 --> 01:23:27,420
Look, l'm driving!

716
01:23:31,940 --> 01:23:33,500
lsn't that fun!

717
01:23:37,180 --> 01:23:38,500
Dear God...

718
01:23:38,700 --> 01:23:41,500
...after many years,
they let Sofia out ofjail...

719
01:23:41,660 --> 01:23:43,620
...just to put her in the next.

720
01:23:44,100 --> 01:23:47,100
She ended up being
Miss Millie's maid after all.

721
01:23:47,780 --> 01:23:52,260
Mayor bought Miss Millie a car,
and she had Sofia teach her how to drive.

722
01:23:53,180 --> 01:23:55,460
Poor Sofia, stuck with Miss Millie...

723
01:23:55,780 --> 01:23:57,580
...for the rest of her life.

724
01:23:57,660 --> 01:23:59,300
We went past the store.

725
01:23:59,500 --> 01:24:02,980
l've got it. Top of the 'H'. Here we go.

726
01:24:12,460 --> 01:24:14,540
That was exciting, wasn't it?

727
01:24:14,820 --> 01:24:17,060
Yes, ma'am, l reckon it was.

728
01:24:19,220 --> 01:24:20,860
Let's do the shopping!

729
01:24:22,860 --> 01:24:26,380
l need apples, raisins,
cinnamon, currants, lemons...

730
01:24:26,700 --> 01:24:30,380
...crackers, sugar, oranges,
nutmeg, flour, salt, pepper...

731
01:24:30,700 --> 01:24:33,700
...cloves, eggs, and some candy
for the children.

732
01:24:43,900 --> 01:24:48,700
l've been wondering about us starting
a fund for the poor colored children....

733
01:25:01,100 --> 01:25:04,020
Sofia's been teaching me how to drive.

734
01:25:04,340 --> 01:25:07,540
Have you ever thought
about going to Mars?

735
01:25:07,860 --> 01:25:09,580
l wonder what it's like.

736
01:25:09,780 --> 01:25:12,820
They call it the red planet.
Does it look red?

737
01:25:25,100 --> 01:25:27,700
How do, Mr. Peters?
Look at me, l'm driving.

738
01:25:39,340 --> 01:25:42,580
Sofia, l'm gonna drive you home tomorrow.

739
01:25:45,420 --> 01:25:48,660
Did you hear what l said?
l'm gonna drive you home.

740
01:25:50,260 --> 01:25:51,100
Home?

741
01:25:51,580 --> 01:25:52,860
Yes, home.

742
01:25:53,260 --> 01:25:55,740
You haven't seen your children in a while.

743
01:25:58,740 --> 01:26:02,060
No, l ain't seen them in about eight years.

744
01:26:03,980 --> 01:26:05,460
That's a shame.

745
01:26:07,420 --> 01:26:11,100
Tomorrow's Christmas!
You can stay all day!

746
01:26:11,180 --> 01:26:13,780
You can stay all day!

747
01:26:17,940 --> 01:26:20,500
l will drive myself back.

748
01:26:31,060 --> 01:26:32,660
Thank you.

749
01:27:09,020 --> 01:27:10,780
That's your mama.

750
01:27:12,700 --> 01:27:13,940
That's her.

751
01:27:20,220 --> 01:27:21,620
Go on.

752
01:27:48,060 --> 01:27:50,300
Hi, my name is Emma.

753
01:27:50,900 --> 01:27:53,460
l'm very pleased to meet you.

754
01:28:28,420 --> 01:28:30,100
l'll pick you up at 5:00.

755
01:28:57,660 --> 01:29:00,860
Oh, Miss Sofia, it's so good
to have you home.

756
01:29:33,380 --> 01:29:34,980
Why're you crying?

757
01:29:37,060 --> 01:29:39,460
'Cause l don't know y'all no more.

758
01:29:57,860 --> 01:30:00,780
l can do it. l can put this thing in reverse.

759
01:30:01,100 --> 01:30:03,020
l can make it go the right way.

760
01:30:04,300 --> 01:30:06,300
She can't get it out of reverse.

761
01:30:45,420 --> 01:30:48,460
You get away from me! Don't touch me!

762
01:30:49,540 --> 01:30:51,620
Don't you know who l am?

763
01:30:52,620 --> 01:30:55,020
l've always been good to you people!

764
01:30:56,380 --> 01:30:57,460
Calm down.

765
01:30:57,540 --> 01:31:00,140
l am Miss Millie! l'm the mayor's wife!

766
01:31:00,540 --> 01:31:02,620
l've always been good to you people!

767
01:31:02,700 --> 01:31:05,380
l've always gone
out of my way for coloreds!

768
01:31:07,180 --> 01:31:09,140
Miss Millie, what's the matter?

769
01:31:11,020 --> 01:31:12,300
Those boys...

770
01:31:12,940 --> 01:31:14,700
...tried to attack me.

771
01:31:15,180 --> 01:31:16,780
No such a thing.

772
01:31:18,220 --> 01:31:21,980
How could you leave me alone for so long?

773
01:31:26,060 --> 01:31:28,940
What am l gonna do about the car?

774
01:31:31,060 --> 01:31:34,220
Jack will drive you home, Miss Millie.

775
01:31:35,980 --> 01:31:40,260
l can't ride in a car with
some strange colored man.

776
01:31:43,820 --> 01:31:46,740
l'll ask my sister Odessa to squeeze in.

777
01:31:47,340 --> 01:31:49,820
That way l have more time
with my children.

778
01:31:56,980 --> 01:31:58,740
l don't know her either.

779
01:32:25,140 --> 01:32:26,420
lt's Shug.

780
01:32:29,260 --> 01:32:31,180
Hot diggidy-dog!

781
01:32:32,420 --> 01:32:34,340
l'm coming, Shug!

782
01:32:34,900 --> 01:32:36,660
-lt's sugarbaby!
-Hey, Shug!

783
01:33:05,780 --> 01:33:09,340
l've heard so much about you!
Feels like we old friends!

784
01:33:24,380 --> 01:33:25,780
This is Grady.

785
01:33:28,380 --> 01:33:29,820
This is my husband.

786
01:33:31,260 --> 01:33:33,340
Us been driving all night.

787
01:33:33,620 --> 01:33:37,940
No place to stop. But here us is!
Well, how are you?

788
01:33:39,100 --> 01:33:40,540
We're fine.

789
01:33:40,860 --> 01:33:42,780
Got colds, though.

790
01:33:46,140 --> 01:33:48,860
This here's my wedding present.
Brand new.

791
01:33:49,140 --> 01:33:51,300
l want Albert to learn how to drive it.

792
01:33:51,380 --> 01:33:54,620
Grady drive like a fool.
l thought the police would get us.

793
01:33:54,780 --> 01:33:58,780
Us two married ladies now.
Two married ladies, and hungry!

794
01:33:59,100 --> 01:34:00,540
What us got to eat?

795
01:34:10,460 --> 01:34:13,780
Yeah, you know, Grady,
we done had the best.

796
01:34:16,380 --> 01:34:18,620
Yeah, we done had the best.

797
01:34:19,100 --> 01:34:21,500
You had her your way. l had her mine.

798
01:34:23,700 --> 01:34:24,940
But we had her!

799
01:34:40,700 --> 01:34:44,220
l'll get my mail. l'm expecting
an agreement from Memphis.

800
01:34:44,540 --> 01:34:46,380
You ought to wait for Mister.

801
01:34:46,460 --> 01:34:49,660
lf l was to wait for Albert,
l'd wait till Christmas.

802
01:35:01,820 --> 01:35:03,740
l's married now!

803
01:35:07,300 --> 01:35:09,660
l said l's married now.

804
01:35:43,260 --> 01:35:45,500
Well, let's toast it at somebody.

805
01:35:45,820 --> 01:35:49,060
All the evil, and all the love.

806
01:36:04,820 --> 01:36:06,580
Come upstairs with me.

807
01:36:06,900 --> 01:36:09,380
l got to finish stuffing the turkey.

808
01:36:13,460 --> 01:36:16,260
You're my kind of man!

809
01:37:38,700 --> 01:37:40,940
''April 18th...

810
01:37:42,220 --> 01:37:43,820
''...1935.

811
01:37:45,900 --> 01:37:47,500
''Dear Celie:

812
01:37:48,620 --> 01:37:51,180
''l know you think l'm dead...

813
01:37:51,500 --> 01:37:53,100
''...but l am not.

814
01:37:54,380 --> 01:37:57,260
''l've been writing to you over the years...

815
01:37:57,580 --> 01:38:00,420
''...but Albert said
you'd never hear from me again...

816
01:38:00,500 --> 01:38:03,500
''...and since l never heard
from you all this time...

817
01:38:03,820 --> 01:38:05,580
''...l guess he was right.

818
01:38:07,220 --> 01:38:10,420
''Now l only write
at Christmas and Easter...

819
01:38:11,180 --> 01:38:15,660
''...hoping my letters get lost among
the Christmas and Easter greetings...

820
01:38:16,020 --> 01:38:20,140
''...or that Albert get the holiday spirit
and have pity on us.

821
01:38:21,460 --> 01:38:23,820
''There is so much to tell you...

822
01:38:24,140 --> 01:38:26,900
''...l hardly know where to begin.

823
01:38:27,380 --> 01:38:31,340
''And anyway, you probably won't
get this letter either.

824
01:38:31,820 --> 01:38:34,580
''l am sure Albert is still the only one...

825
01:38:34,900 --> 01:38:37,060
''...to take the mail out of the box.

826
01:38:38,100 --> 01:38:40,940
''But if this does not get to him...

827
01:38:41,740 --> 01:38:43,980
''...one thing l want you to know...

828
01:38:46,900 --> 01:38:48,460
''...l love you...

829
01:38:49,460 --> 01:38:51,980
''...and l'm not dead.''

830
01:38:57,740 --> 01:39:00,340
l love you and am not dead.

831
01:39:01,260 --> 01:39:05,060
''The lady you met in town
is named Corrine.

832
01:39:06,100 --> 01:39:07,980
''Her husband's named Samuel.

833
01:39:10,060 --> 01:39:13,860
''Sanctified religious and very good to me.

834
01:39:14,900 --> 01:39:17,580
''Their only sorrow in the beginning was...

835
01:39:17,900 --> 01:39:20,660
''...that they could not have children.

836
01:39:20,980 --> 01:39:23,220
''Then they say....

837
01:39:27,700 --> 01:39:29,140
''Then they say...

838
01:39:31,780 --> 01:39:34,620
''...God sent them Olivia...

839
01:39:36,340 --> 01:39:37,940
''...and Adam.

840
01:39:42,940 --> 01:39:46,100
''Yes, their children sent by God
are your children.

841
01:39:49,020 --> 01:39:52,660
''And they have been brought up in love.

842
01:39:53,620 --> 01:39:56,860
''And now God has sent me
to watch over them...

843
01:39:57,180 --> 01:39:59,580
''...to protect and cherish them...

844
01:39:59,860 --> 01:40:03,420
''...to lavish all the love
l feel for you on them.

845
01:40:04,340 --> 01:40:06,620
''lt's a miracle, isn't it?

846
01:40:06,940 --> 01:40:10,100
''And no doubt impossible
for you to believe.

847
01:40:10,460 --> 01:40:13,140
''Olivia and Adam are with me...

848
01:40:13,460 --> 01:40:15,700
''...all growing up together...

849
01:40:16,220 --> 01:40:17,780
''...a family.

850
01:40:19,420 --> 01:40:21,500
''Your loving sister, Nettie.''

851
01:40:32,700 --> 01:40:34,780
l got two children...

852
01:40:36,700 --> 01:40:38,460
...and they's alive.

853
01:40:39,860 --> 01:40:41,460
Hear that Miss Shug?

854
01:40:43,260 --> 01:40:45,900
Olivia...and Adam.

855
01:40:51,860 --> 01:40:53,460
And they's alive.

856
01:42:00,220 --> 01:42:02,660
l's getting real tired of this cat.

857
01:42:08,140 --> 01:42:09,580
He coming back soon.

858
01:42:09,900 --> 01:42:11,980
You crazy? He in the jook joint.

859
01:42:51,460 --> 01:42:53,540
This doesn't look nothing like me.

860
01:42:53,700 --> 01:42:55,180
Damn him.

861
01:43:59,020 --> 01:44:00,660
There's so many of them.

862
01:44:00,940 --> 01:44:02,340
What us gonna do?

863
01:44:03,500 --> 01:44:06,700
Go to my room and put them
in order by the postmark.

864
01:44:09,300 --> 01:44:13,580
''Dear Celie, the reason why
l am in Africa is because...

865
01:44:13,900 --> 01:44:18,420
''...one of the missionaries who was
supposed to go with Corrine and Samuel...

866
01:44:18,500 --> 01:44:22,380
''...to help with the children
and setting up the school...

867
01:44:22,700 --> 01:44:26,380
''...suddenly married a man,
and l came in her place.''

868
01:44:26,740 --> 01:44:29,740
I wrote a letter to you
almost every day on the ship.

869
01:44:30,060 --> 01:44:32,660
On my first sight of the Africa coast...

870
01:44:32,980 --> 01:44:37,140
...something struck in my soul,
like a large bell.

871
01:44:37,460 --> 01:44:38,740
Ijust vibrated.

872
01:44:53,620 --> 01:44:58,260
It has been a long time since
I had time to write, but always...

873
01:44:58,620 --> 01:45:02,460
...no matter what I'm doing,
I'm writing you. Dear--

874
01:45:02,780 --> 01:45:05,140
Celie! Bring me a cool drink.

875
01:45:15,700 --> 01:45:19,020
Olinka is four days march
through the bush from the harbor.

876
01:45:19,260 --> 01:45:21,180
Do you know what ajungle is?

877
01:45:21,460 --> 01:45:25,300
Trees and trees and more trees
on top of that.

878
01:45:25,780 --> 01:45:29,300
They are so big,
they look like they were built.

879
01:45:29,620 --> 01:45:33,500
And vines and ferns
and animals and noises...

880
01:45:33,820 --> 01:45:37,500
...that make you wonder
what is lurking behind the shadows...

881
01:45:37,780 --> 01:45:39,420
...of every bush.

882
01:45:45,940 --> 01:45:47,500
We're up at 5:00...

883
01:45:47,700 --> 01:45:51,700
...for a breakfast of millet,
porridge and fruit, then morning classes.

884
01:45:52,020 --> 01:45:55,100
We teach the children English,
reading, writing...

885
01:45:55,420 --> 01:45:59,260
...history, geography,
arithmetic and Bible stories.

886
01:46:04,700 --> 01:46:07,620
The older children are
used to going to mission school.

887
01:46:07,700 --> 01:46:09,340
The smaller ones are not.

888
01:46:09,660 --> 01:46:13,500
Their mothers drag them here
screaming and kicking.

889
01:46:13,820 --> 01:46:17,340
They're all boys. Olivia's the only girl.

890
01:46:28,740 --> 01:46:31,300
There is a little African girl called Tashi.

891
01:46:31,580 --> 01:46:33,500
She plays with Olivia.

892
01:46:33,820 --> 01:46:36,420
''Why can't Tashi come to school?''
She asked me.

893
01:46:36,740 --> 01:46:40,260
I told her the Olinka don't believe
in educating girls.

894
01:46:40,580 --> 01:46:42,420
She said, quick as a flash:

895
01:46:42,500 --> 01:46:46,300
''Like white people at home
who don't want black people to learn. ''

896
01:46:46,980 --> 01:46:49,060
She is sharp, Celie.

897
01:46:49,380 --> 01:46:52,380
When Tashi can get away
from her chores...

898
01:46:52,740 --> 01:46:55,140
...she and Olivia hide in my hut.

899
01:46:55,460 --> 01:46:58,660
To Olivia right now, Tashi alone is Africa....

900
01:46:58,980 --> 01:47:03,580
Everything she learns, she shares
with Tashi. Sound familiar?

901
01:47:18,300 --> 01:47:22,980
At first, there was the faintest
sound of movement in the forest.

902
01:47:23,300 --> 01:47:27,900
A kind of low humming.
Then chopping and the sound of dragging.

903
01:47:28,260 --> 01:47:30,980
Then the scent. Some days there's smoke.

904
01:47:31,300 --> 01:47:34,340
Now, after two months
during which I or the children...

905
01:47:34,460 --> 01:47:36,380
...or Corrine has been sick...

906
01:47:36,700 --> 01:47:39,700
...all we hear is chopping
and scraping and dragging.

907
01:47:39,900 --> 01:47:42,300
Every day we smell smoke.

908
01:47:42,780 --> 01:47:46,820
Today a boy in my afternoon
class burst out as he entered:

909
01:47:47,100 --> 01:47:49,380
''The road approaches!''

910
01:47:57,500 --> 01:48:01,420
Dear Celie, the white man
is building a road.

911
01:48:01,940 --> 01:48:04,500
It reached the cassava
fields nine months ago.

912
01:48:05,340 --> 01:48:09,260
The morning after the road was done,
as far as Olinka was concerned...

913
01:48:09,540 --> 01:48:13,100
...what should we discover,
but that the road builders were back.

914
01:48:13,540 --> 01:48:18,220
They have instructions to continue
the road for another 30 miles...

915
01:48:18,700 --> 01:48:23,180
...and continue it right
through the village of Olinka.

916
01:48:35,620 --> 01:48:40,300
The road builders didn't deviate
an inch from the head man's plan.

917
01:48:40,620 --> 01:48:43,020
Every hut that lay in the road's path...

918
01:48:43,340 --> 01:48:44,740
...was leveled.

919
01:48:45,020 --> 01:48:48,300
Celie, our church, our school...

920
01:48:49,100 --> 01:48:50,660
...my hut...

921
01:48:51,020 --> 01:48:53,260
...all went down in a matter of hours.

922
01:49:03,020 --> 01:49:05,380
But the worst is yet to be told.

923
01:49:06,220 --> 01:49:10,020
Sweet Corrine...died from fever and grief.

924
01:49:11,820 --> 01:49:14,340
We buried her in the Olinka way.

925
01:49:17,580 --> 01:49:19,940
But Celie, my dear sweet sister...

926
01:49:20,260 --> 01:49:25,060
...we'll all be coming home once we work
something out with U.S. Immigration.

927
01:49:25,260 --> 01:49:28,940
They don't know if we're American,
African, or missionary.

928
01:49:29,420 --> 01:49:31,340
Just pray for us, Celie.

929
01:49:31,660 --> 01:49:34,220
Watch for me in the sunset.

930
01:49:39,020 --> 01:49:42,060
What's with you?
l was calling you for an hour!

931
01:49:42,380 --> 01:49:44,980
Now get my shave
and don't keep me waiting!

932
01:49:49,300 --> 01:49:51,820
-Where's Celie?
-Home fixing to shave Mister.

933
01:50:18,580 --> 01:50:23,060
You got a fever? l didn't come here
for you to take all day to shave me.

934
01:50:23,980 --> 01:50:26,380
Get the molasses out of your ass!

935
01:50:59,940 --> 01:51:03,940
The longer l'm married to you,
the slower and dumber you get.

936
01:51:04,660 --> 01:51:08,180
Your ass as slow as l ever seen it before.

937
01:51:34,900 --> 01:51:37,660
Celie! Ain't that razor sharpened yet?

938
01:51:38,260 --> 01:51:41,500
Get out here and do me right now!
Get out here!

939
01:51:46,940 --> 01:51:48,100
All right.

940
01:52:29,180 --> 01:52:30,620
Put your head back.

941
01:52:45,340 --> 01:52:47,900
Cut my neck and l'll get you by the ears.

942
01:53:01,660 --> 01:53:04,060
That razor looks dull to me, Miss Celie.

943
01:53:13,380 --> 01:53:14,900
Damn women.

944
01:53:36,700 --> 01:53:38,980
How you feeling, Miss Sofia?

945
01:53:39,620 --> 01:53:41,220
Confused.

946
01:53:41,700 --> 01:53:43,460
Ain't you glad to be home?

947
01:53:45,060 --> 01:53:46,300
Maybe.

948
01:53:56,220 --> 01:53:58,780
-Now come the time for me to tell you.
-What?

949
01:54:01,220 --> 01:54:02,980
lt's time for us to go.

950
01:54:03,300 --> 01:54:06,980
You're such good people. Salt of the earth.

951
01:54:07,260 --> 01:54:08,860
lt's time to move on.

952
01:54:09,060 --> 01:54:10,980
-Celie is coming with us.
-What?

953
01:54:12,900 --> 01:54:15,420
Celie is coming to Memphis with us.

954
01:54:15,740 --> 01:54:17,700
Over my dead body!

955
01:54:18,020 --> 01:54:20,420
You satisfied? That's what you want?

956
01:54:21,220 --> 01:54:23,140
Now what's wrong with you?

957
01:54:24,420 --> 01:54:26,980
You a lowdown, dirty dog,
that's what's wrong.

958
01:54:28,580 --> 01:54:30,980
lt's time for me to get away from you...

959
01:54:31,140 --> 01:54:32,740
...and enter Creation.

960
01:54:33,060 --> 01:54:35,460
Your dead body be
the welcome mat l need.

961
01:54:35,620 --> 01:54:38,340
You can't talk to my boy that way.

962
01:54:38,620 --> 01:54:39,860
Your boy.

963
01:54:40,260 --> 01:54:43,900
lf he hadn't been your boy
he might have been a halfway decent man.

964
01:54:44,260 --> 01:54:45,580
Say what?

965
01:54:45,900 --> 01:54:48,260
You took my sister Nettie away from me.

966
01:54:50,500 --> 01:54:54,340
You knew she was the only person
in the world who loved me.

967
01:54:59,020 --> 01:55:01,540
But Nettie and my kids
are coming home soon.

968
01:55:01,860 --> 01:55:05,860
And when we get together,
we're going to whip your ass.

969
01:55:08,580 --> 01:55:12,100
Nettie and your kids?
Woman, you talking crazy.

970
01:55:12,740 --> 01:55:16,860
l got children.
My children are living in Africa.

971
01:55:18,180 --> 01:55:21,580
Africa! Learning different languages.

972
01:55:22,180 --> 01:55:24,620
Fresh air, plenty of exercise.

973
01:55:25,260 --> 01:55:29,380
They'll turn out better
than these fools you never tried to raise.

974
01:55:29,700 --> 01:55:32,140
-Hold on here!
-No ''hold on'', Harpo.

975
01:55:32,900 --> 01:55:37,100
lf you hadn't tried to rule over Sofia,
white folks wouldn't have got her.

976
01:55:37,420 --> 01:55:39,820
-That's a lie!
-And a little truth in it.

977
01:55:41,860 --> 01:55:46,180
Y'all was rotten kids.
You was. You was rotten kids!

978
01:55:49,420 --> 01:55:51,340
Made my life here hell.

979
01:55:52,620 --> 01:55:55,980
Your daddy ain't nothing
but some dead horseshit.

980
01:56:01,580 --> 01:56:02,300
Shut up!

981
01:56:02,380 --> 01:56:04,900
lt's bad luck for a woman
to laugh at a man!

982
01:56:23,540 --> 01:56:26,060
My God, the dead has arisen.

983
01:56:29,300 --> 01:56:34,060
l had enough bad luck to keep me
laughing the rest of my life.

984
01:56:35,980 --> 01:56:40,300
Sitting in that jail,
l near about done rot to death.

985
01:56:42,580 --> 01:56:44,940
l know what it like, Miss Celie.

986
01:56:45,300 --> 01:56:47,540
Want to go somewhere and can't.

987
01:56:49,300 --> 01:56:53,900
l know what it like to want to
sing and have it beat out of you.

988
01:56:55,220 --> 01:56:57,740
l want to thank you, Miss Celie...

989
01:56:58,220 --> 01:57:00,820
...for everything you done for me.

990
01:57:02,060 --> 01:57:05,580
l remember the day
l was in the store with Miss Millie.

991
01:57:06,740 --> 01:57:10,860
l was feeling real down.
l was feeling mighty bad.

992
01:57:12,300 --> 01:57:14,380
And when l see'd you...

993
01:57:15,540 --> 01:57:17,900
...l knowed there is a god.

994
01:57:18,900 --> 01:57:23,660
l knowed there is a god, and one day
l was going to get to come home.

995
01:57:24,980 --> 01:57:27,940
You won't get a penny of my money.
Not one thin dime!

996
01:57:28,140 --> 01:57:31,220
Did l ever ask you for anything?

997
01:57:31,540 --> 01:57:34,100
Not even for your sorry-ass hand
in marriage!

998
01:57:34,420 --> 01:57:36,340
l never asked you for nothing!

999
01:57:39,060 --> 01:57:42,100
Old Sofia home now. Sofia home.

1000
01:57:42,420 --> 01:57:44,740
Things are going to change around here.

1001
01:57:44,820 --> 01:57:46,420
l'm going with Shug.

1002
01:57:47,380 --> 01:57:48,820
You going where?

1003
01:57:49,100 --> 01:57:50,860
With Miss Celie and Shug.

1004
01:57:51,060 --> 01:57:53,180
l'm fixing to sing.

1005
01:57:53,780 --> 01:57:56,940
Too much racket going on in this house.
Pass me the peas.

1006
01:57:57,340 --> 01:57:58,660
Listen, Squeak--

1007
01:57:58,980 --> 01:58:00,900
-My name ain't Squeak.
-What?

1008
01:58:02,900 --> 01:58:04,580
My name is Mary Agnes.

1009
01:58:04,860 --> 01:58:05,860
Mary what?

1010
01:58:05,940 --> 01:58:07,740
Mary Agnes.

1011
01:58:08,180 --> 01:58:09,700
l thought it was Squeak.

1012
01:58:09,780 --> 01:58:13,940
Who cares?
Boy, you going to let this nappy-head gal...

1013
01:58:14,260 --> 01:58:17,460
...cuss you out?
You're at the head of your own table...

1014
01:58:17,700 --> 01:58:19,180
...and you acting like a waiter!

1015
01:58:19,260 --> 01:58:23,420
Hush, you old fool!
Always meddling in somebody's business.

1016
01:58:25,660 --> 01:58:29,660
She'll be back. Shug got talent.
She can sing.

1017
01:58:30,580 --> 01:58:35,260
She got spunk and can talk to anybody.
She can stand up and be noticed.

1018
01:58:35,700 --> 01:58:36,900
What you got?

1019
01:58:37,620 --> 01:58:40,380
You're ugly. You're skinny.
You're shaped funny.

1020
01:58:40,540 --> 01:58:43,180
You're too scared to open
your mouth to people.

1021
01:58:43,420 --> 01:58:45,980
All you fit to do is be Shug's maid.

1022
01:58:46,260 --> 01:58:47,340
Albert, no.

1023
01:58:47,580 --> 01:58:52,180
Take out her slop jar, maybe cook her food.
You ain't even that good a cook.

1024
01:58:52,500 --> 01:58:55,740
She's a lot better
than that first wife of yours.

1025
